The carcinoma measured 5.7 cm in greatest diameter and , therefore , is pathologically staged as a pT2b .

Two peribronchial lymph nodes in the right lung resection ( specimen three } as well as a small area from random section from the right upper lobe parenchyma in 3M show focal degeneration and necrosis with surrounding chronic granulomatous inflammation and fibrosis .

A GMS stain is performed which demonstrates no fungal organisms ( with appropriate positive control ) .

Specimen two , submitted as lymph node level 7 right chest , and specimen four , submitted as lymph node level 8 right chest , both are received as fragmented to partially fragmented soft tissue and , therefore , an accurate node count can not be performed .
No metastatic carcinoma is identified .
